    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-03-31T17:23:45+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-31T17:23:45+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-31T06:53:45Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-31T06:53:45Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A trough over western SA, links to a low pressure system well south of the Bight. The low and associated trough continue to move southeastwards, with the trough reaching central parts late Tuesday and then pushing into the northeast of SA on Wednesday. A high pressure system is expected to become established south of the Bight late in the week, after a weak front clips the southeast late Thursday.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW010" description="West Coast" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-03-31T15:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-01T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-31T04:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-31T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Very high chance of showers east of Ceduna, high chance elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm, possibly severe with damaging winds and heavy rain which may lead to flash flooding. Winds north to northwesterly 25 to 35 km/h shifting south to southwesterly 20 to 30 km/h in the late afternoon.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-04-01T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-02T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-31T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-01T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. Slight chance of a shower east of Ceduna in the early morning. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm in the early morning. Winds south to southwesterly 15 to 20 km/h becoming light in the early morning then becoming southeast to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h in the morning. Overnight temperatures falling to between 13 and 16 with daytime temperatures reaching the low to mid 20s.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">Moderate</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 10:30am to 4:40pm, UV Index predicted to reach 7 [High]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-04-02T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-03T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-01T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-02T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. Light winds becoming east to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h in the morning then tending south to southeasterly 20 to 30 km/h in the middle of the day. Overnight temperatures falling to between 10 and 13 with daytime temperatures reaching the low to mid 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-04-03T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-04T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-02T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-03T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog south of Streaky Bay. Medium chance of showers west of Nullarbor, most likely in the morning. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Winds southeasterly 15 to 25 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to between 11 and 14 with daytime temperatures reaching the low to mid 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-04-04T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-05T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-03T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-04T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. Medium chance of showers west of Nullarbor, near zero chance elsewhere. Winds east to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h tending east to northeasterly during the morning then tending east to southeasterly during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 12 and 15 with daytime temperatures reaching around 30.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
